ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Have you smoked at least 100 cigarettes in your entire life? PX030601_Cigarette_Smoking_100
Notes: 1=Yes; 2=No; 97=Don't Know/Refused

ElementDescription: Have you smoked at least part of a cigarette in the last 7 days?
Notes: 0 = No; 1 = Yes

ElementDescription: Now think about the past 30 days, including today. During the past 30 days, have you smoked part or all of a roll-your-own tobacco cigarette? PX030801_30Day_Cigarette_Smoking
Notes: 1=Yes; 2=No; 99=DK/refused

ElementDescription: During a typical 7-day period; how many cigarettes do you smoke per day? (cigarettes per day)
During the past 30 days; how many days per week or per month did you have at least one drink of any alcoholic beverage?
Past 30 days, frequency of having at least one drink measured per week or per month?
Notes: (1=per week; 2=in the last 30 days)

ElementDescription: On the days when you drank; about how many drinks did you drink on average? (drinks)
Considering all types of alcoholic beverages; how many times during the past 30 days did you have five or more drinks on an occasion? (times)
How many times a week do you eat fast food or snacks?
Notes: 1=Less than 1; 2=1-3 times; 3=4 or more

ElementDescription: How many servings of fruit and/or vegetables do you eat each day?
Notes: 1=5 or more; 2=3-4 servings; 3=2 or less

ElementDescription: How many regular soft drinks (sodas or glasses of sweet tea) do you drink each day (1 glass = 8oz)
Notes: 1=Less than 1; 2=1-2 glasses; 3 or more

ElementDescription: How many times a week do you eat chicken; fish; or beans (like pinto beans or black beans)?
Notes: 1=3 or more; 2=1-2 times; 3=Less than 1

ElementDescription: How many times a week do you eat regular snack chips or crackers (not low-fat)?
Notes: 1=1 or less; 2=2-3 times; 3=4 or more

ElementDescription: How many times a week do you eat desserts or other sweets?
Notes: 1=1 or less; 2=2-3 times; 3=4 or more

ElementDescription: How much margarine; butter; or meat fat do you use to season vegetables; potatoes; bread; or corn?
Notes: 1=Very little; 2=Some; 3=A lot

ElementDescription: During the last 7 days, on how many days did you do vigorous physical activities like heavy lifting, digging, aerobics, or fast cycling? (# days per week)
Notes: Number of days vigorous activity was completed; -997 = Missing; -998 = Not collected at this time point

ElementDescription: How much time did you usually spend doing vigorous physical activities on one of those days? (hours per day)
Notes: -997 = Missing; -998 = Not collected at this time point; -999 = Not applicable

ElementDescription: How much time did you usually spend doing vigorous physical activities on one of those days? (minutes per day)
Notes: Minutes of vigorous activity per day; 999= Unknown; -997 = Missing; -998 = Not collected at this time point; -999 = Not applicable

ElementDescription: During the last 7 days, on how many days did you do moderate physical activities like carrying light loads, bicycling at a regular pace, or doubles tennis? (# days per week)
Notes: Number of days completing moderate activity; -997 = Missing; -998 = Not collected at this time point

ElementDescription: How much time did you usually spend doing moderate physical activities on one of those days? (hours per day)
Notes: -997 = Missing; -998 = Not collected at this time point; -999 = Not applicable

ElementDescription: How much time did you usually spend doing moderate physical activities on one of those days? (minutes per day)
Notes: Minutes of moderate activity per day; 999= Unknown; -997 = Missing; -998 = Not collected at this time point; -999 = Not applicable

ElementDescription: During  the  last 7 days, on how many days did you walk for at least 10 minutes at a time to go from place to place (days per week)
How much time did you usually spend walking on one of those days? (hours per day)
Notes: -997 = Missing; -998 = Not collected at this time point; -999 = Not applicable

ElementDescription: How much time did you usually spend walking on one of those days? (minutes per day)
Notes: Minutes of walking per day; 999= Unknown; -997 = Missing; -998 = Not collected at this time point; -999 = Not applicable

ElementDescription: During the last 7 days, how much time did you spend sitting on a week day? (hours per day)
Notes: Hours of sitting time per week day; -997 = Missing; -998 = Not collected at this time point

ElementDescription: During the last 7 days, how much time did you spend sitting on a week day? (minutes per day)
Notes: 999 = Unknown; -997 = Missing; -998 = Not collected at this time point

ElementDescription: Overall risk score
Don't know/not sure (How much time did you usually spend doing vigorous physical activities on one of those days?)
Notes: 1 = Unknown amount of time spent on vigorous physical activities

ElementDescription: Don't know/not sure(How much time did you usually spend doing moderate physical activities on one of those days?)
Notes: 1 = Unknown amount of time spent on moderate physical activities

ElementDescription: Don't know/not sure(How much time did you usually spend walking on one of those days?)
Notes: 1 = Unknown amount of time spent walking

ElementDescription: Don't know/not sure(During the past 7 days, how much time did you spend sitting on a week day.)
Notes: 1 = Unknown amount of time spent sitting on a weekday

ElementDescription: No vigorous physical activities  (During the past 7 days, on how many days did you do vigorous physical activities like heavy lifting, digging, aerobics, or fast bicycling?)
Notes: 1 = Engaged in no vigorous physical activites

ElementDescription: No moderate physical activities  (During the past 7 days, on how many days did you do moderate physical activities like carrying light loads, bicycling at a regular pace, or doubles tennis? Do not include walking.)
Notes: 1 = Engaged in no moderate physical activites

ElementDescription: No walking  (During the past 7 days, on how many days did you walk for at least 10 minutes at a time.)
Notes: 1 = Engaged in no walking
